<subSubSection id="C330652C8819FFCB48F2FCB5FA7FD03F" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" type="key">
<key id="FFBB61968819FFCB48F2FCB5FA7FD03F" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyStep id="30DE2E028819FFCB48F2FCB5FA7FD6B1" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FCB5FA7FD6AC" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" box="[136,1451,875,897]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FCB5FA7FD6AC" box="[136,1451,875,897]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">1. Plants usually prostrate or at least some branches prostrate...............................................................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FC56FA7FD6B1" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" box="[136,1451,903,925]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FC56FA7FD6B1" box="[136,1451,903,925]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">1’. Plants erect..........................................................................................................................................................................................4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30DE2E028819FFCB48F2FC7AFA7FD6FA" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FC7AFA7FD695" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" box="[136,1451,932,954]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FC7AFA7FD695" box="[136,1451,932,954]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
2. Inflorescence axis elongated. Flowers alternate on axis (up to 40)............................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D248819FFCB4D6AFC7BFA7FD695" box="[1296,1451,932,954]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Petalidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustitubum">
<emphasis id="B95EEAB58819FFCB4D6AFC7BFA7FD695" box="[1296,1451,932,954]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">P. angustitubum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FC1FFA7FD6FA" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" box="[136,1451,961,983]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FC1FFA7FD6FA" box="[136,1451,961,983]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">2’. Inflorescence compact balls ...............................................................................................................................................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30DE2E028819FFCB48F2FC00FA7FD13C" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FC00FA7ED6DF" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" box="[136,1450,990,1012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FC00FA7ED6DF" box="[136,1450,990,1012]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
3. Leaf lamina ca. 1.5× as long as wide or more compact, broadly ovate.......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D248819FFCB4D50FC00FA7ED6DF" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1880" box="[1322,1450,990,1011]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Petalidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="halimoides">
<emphasis id="B95EEAB58819FFCB4D50FC00FA7ED6DF" box="[1322,1450,990,1011]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">P. halimoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FC25FA7FD13C" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" box="[136,1451,1018,1041]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FC25FA7FD13C" box="[136,1451,1018,1041]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
3’. Leaf lamina ca. 2.5× as long as wide or thinner, narrowly ovate........................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D248819FFCB4D3EFC25FA7FD13C" authorityName="Clarke" authorityYear="1899" box="[1348,1451,1019,1040]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Petalidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanatum">
<emphasis id="B95EEAB58819FFCB4D3EFC25FA7FD13C" box="[1348,1451,1019,1040]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">P. lanatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30DE2E028819FFCB48F2FBC6FA7FD14B" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FBC6FA7FD101" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" box="[136,1451,1047,1069]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FBC6FA7FD101" box="[136,1451,1047,1069]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">4. Indumentum on leaves consisting of simple trichomes, erect or appressed (strigose).......................................................................5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FBEAFA7FD14B" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FBEAFA7FD14B" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">4’. Indumentum on leaves consisting of dendritic or stellate trichomes interspersed with very short-stalked glandular trichomes ........ ............................................................................................................................................................................................................6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30DE2E028819FFCB48F2FBB0FA7FD190" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FBB0FA7FD1AF" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" box="[136,1451,1134,1156]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FBB0FA7FD1AF" box="[136,1451,1134,1156]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
5. Trichomes erect, corolla tube distinctively curved, corolla lobes one-coloured red....................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D248819FFCB4D57FBB0FA7FD1AF" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1880" box="[1325,1451,1134,1155]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Petalidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coccineum">
<emphasis id="B95EEAB58819FFCB4D57FBB0FA7FD1AF" box="[1325,1451,1134,1155]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">P. coccineum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FB54FA7FD190" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FB54FA7FD190" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
5’. Trichomes appressed, corolla tube straight, front corolla lobe differently coloured or of darker shade than other lobes: white, pink, or crimson; other lobes: brown, orange, pink, or crimson................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D248819FFCB4D47FB76FA7FD190" box="[1341,1451,1191,1213]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Petalidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variabile">
<emphasis id="B95EEAB58819FFCB4D47FB76FA7FD190" box="[1341,1451,1191,1213]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">P. variabile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30DE2E028819FFCB48F2FB1AFA7FD03F" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FB1AFA7FD1DA" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FB1AFA7FD1DA" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
6. Indumentum consisting of short-stalked stellate trichomes interspersed with very short-stalked glandular trichomes; expanded portion of corolla strigose outside ................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D248819FFCB4D55FB3CFA7FD1DA" authorityName="Swanepoel" authorityYear="2020" box="[1327,1451,1249,1271]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Petalidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kaokoense">
<emphasis id="B95EEAB58819FFCB4D55FB3CFA7FD1DA" box="[1327,1451,1249,1271]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">P. kaokoense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9536A78819FFCB48F2FB20FA7FD03F" blockId="7.[136,1452,875,1300]" box="[136,1451,1278,1300]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
<keyLead id="30DB95928819FFCB48F2FB20FA7FD03F" box="[136,1451,1278,1300]" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">
6’. Indumentum consisting of dendritic trichomes only; expanded portion of corolla glabrous outside ....................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A4D248819FFCB4D73FB20FA7FD03F" authorityName="Swanepoel &amp; E. Tripp" authorityYear="2022" box="[1289,1451,1278,1299]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Petalidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sesfonteinense">
<emphasis id="B95EEAB58819FFCB4D73FB20FA7FD03F" box="[1289,1451,1278,1299]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="134">P. sesfonteinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
